{"word":"ἐντρέπω","slug":"ἐντρέπω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐντρέπω</b></el> <el>(<a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <el>-τρέψω</el>) </el><p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to turn about</i> <el>τὰ νῶτα</el> <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>: <i>to alter</i>, <b><a href='S:Lucian'>Luc.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a> or <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a>, aor2 <el>ἐνετράπην [ᾰ]</el>, <i>to turn about, linger, hesitate</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a> <a href='S:person, personal'>pers.</a> <i>to turn towards, give heed to, pay regard to, to respect</i> or <i>reverence</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Tragic, in Tragic Greek'>Trag.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a> <i>to take care that</i>, <b><a href='S:Theognis'>Theogn.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>4. </b><a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a> <i>to feel shame</i> or <i>fear</i>, <b><a href='S:New Testament'>NTest.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}